@node "Overview" "Overview"

    @{b}ASCII_SEND@{ub} is a Tool, which can conver any given textfile
    to a stream of @{" InputEvents " link "InputEvents" 0}. These InputEvents are sent to the active
    Window or (via the Arexx-Port of MUI_ASCSEND) any window you made
    the active one.

    It is a Commodity, in which you can assign a filename to a
(user-defined)
    hotkey. On pressing this key, the file is converted to Inputevents.
    
    There is also an InputEvent-Recorder (IREC) available, which does this
thing
    the backward way: it converts Keystrokes and Mousebuttons to a 
    textfile.

@endnode

@node "System requirements" "System requirements"

      For all of the programs OS2.04+ is necessary.
      MUI_ASCSEND needs at least MUI 2.0 (Library V7+), it is
      localized under WB2.1+.

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

      Just move the executables anywhere you like. It is recommendet that
      you keep the things you need in the wbstartup-drawer.
      If you use MUI_ASCSEND you will of course need a properly installed
      MUI V2.0+. If you want to use the english Version of MUI_ASCSEND    
      copy the file catalogs/english/asccsend.catalog to your 
      LOCALE:catalogs/english/ drawer.

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
    
     
    all executables  (ASCSEND,MUI_ASCSEND und IREC) are to be 
    used with Icon-TOOLTYPES, except for MUI_ASCSEND, which has
    a GUI. The TOOLTYPES can also be given on a commandline.

    CLI_ASCSEND doesn't accept TOOLTYPES, you have to use this
    program from a shell.

    Tooltypes for both ASCII_SEND and MUI_ASCIISEND are :

             @{"  HOTKEY[x]  " link "hotkey" 0}
             @{"  FILE[x]    " link "file" 0}
             @{"  REQUESTKEY " link "requestkey" 0}
             @{"  REQPATH    " link "reqpath" 0}
             @{"  REQFILE    " link "reqfile" 0}
             @{"  STOPKEY    " link "stopkey" 0}
             @{"  DELAY      " link "delay" 0}
             @{"  DELAYCHAR  " link "delaychar" 0}
             @{"  INFOKEY    " link "infokey" 0}
 
    Tooltypes only recognized by MUI_ASCSEND and IREC are:

             @{"  RECSTARTKEY      " link "recstart" 0}
             @{"  RECSTOPKEY       " link "recstop" 0}
             @{"  RECFILE          " link "recfile" 0}
             @{"  MIN_DELAY        " link "min_delay" 0}
             @{"  HANDLER_PRIORITY " link "h_priority" 0}
             @{"  INCLUDE_MB       " link "include_mb" 0}
             @{"  INCLUDE_DELAY    " link "include_delay" 0}
             @{"  REC_MAXCHAR      " link "rec_maxchar" 0}
             @{"  REC_MAX_ON       " link "rec_max_on" 0}

   the Tooltype

             @{"  WAIT             " link "irec_wait" 0}

    is only recognized by IREC and
    

             @{"  CX_POPUP    " link "popkey" 0}
             @{"  EDITOR      " link "editor" 0}

    are for MUI_ASCSEND only.

    The textfiles you send may contain other special @{" InputEvents " link "InputEvents" 0}
    
    For details read the @{"MUI-ASCII_SEND" link "mui-ASCII_SEND" 0}"} and 
    @{"CLI_ASCSEND" link "cli_ascsend" 0} chapters

    You can quit ASCII_SEND by
     
    1. by starting it twice        (MUI_ASCIISEND doesn't quit, it opens its
window
                                   instead.     
                                
    2. using Commodities-Exchange->Remove

    3. by opening the  @{" Info-Requester " link "infokey" 0}
       and selecting "Quit"

@endnode

@node "hotkey" "hotkey"

      USAGE :
      
      HOTKEY[x]=hotkey
      
      Example:
      
      HOTKEY0=control alt 1
      
      Defines a hotkey als control-alt-1. To use a hotkey, you have
      to attach a file (using the @{" File" link "file" 0}-Tooltype)
      to it. 
      You can have as many hotkeys as you like, but the numbers have
      to be succesive.

@endnode

@node "file" "file"

      USAGE :
      
      FILE[x]=dateiname
      
      Example
      
      FILE0=work:test/unfug
      
      this file is attached to the @{" Hotkey " link "hotkey" 0} 0 
      and will be sent, when the hotkey is pressed.
      You can have as many hotkeys as you like, but the numbers have
      to be succesive.


@endnode

@node "requestkey" "requestkey"

      REQUESTKEY=hotkey

      This hotkey opens a filerequester. If you chose a file, the window
      which was active before the requester will be activated.
      You can supply defaults for path and filename using the       
      @{"REQPATH" link "Heddley_Error" 0} and @{"REQFILE" link "Heddley_Error" 0} tooltypes        

      ********* Attention ****************
      
      This function does not check if the window to activate  
      exists !! DO NOT CLOSE THIS WINDOW !
    
      ********************************      

@endnode

@node "reqpath" "reqpath"

      REQPATH=pfad
      
      Default path in the filerequester      
      see also  @{"REQESTKEY" link "Heddley_Error" 0}

@endnode

@node "reqfile" "reqfile"

      REQFILE=Dateiname
      
      default filename in the filerequester      
      see also  @{"REQESTKEY" link "Heddley_Error" 0}

@endnode

@node "stopkey" "stopkey"
    
      STOPKEY=hotkey
      
      this hotkey stops transferring a file.      
      
      Example: STOPKEY=control alt 3
      

@endnode

@node "delay" "delay"

      DELAY=x
     
      global delay between single lines of a file in 1/50s.
      Defaults to 12 (1/4s). 
      see also the @{"DELAYCHAR" link "Heddley_Error" 0} tooltype
      and the  @{" \d Inputevent" link "Heddley_Error" 0} chapter

@endnode

@node "delaychar" "delaychar"

      DELAYCHAR=x

      global delay between single characters of a file in 1/50s.
      Defaults to 0 (no delay). 
      see also the @{"DELAY" link "Heddley_Error" 0} tooltype
      and the  @{" \d Inputevent" link "Heddley_Error" 0} chapter

@endnode

@node "infokey" "infokey"

      INFOKEY=hotkey
     
      Show the Info-Requester.

@endnode

@node "popkey" "popkey"


      CX_POPUP=hotkey         (MUI_ASCSEND only)

      opens the MUI_ASCSEND-window and stops transferring files.
      

@endnode

@node "editor" "editor"
     
      EDITOR=editor           (MUI_ASCSEND only)
            
      Editor to use.

@endnode

@node "recstart" "recstart"
  
      RECSTARTKEY=taste       (MUI_ASCSEND and  IREC only )

      starts recording keystrokes
      to stop press the @{"RECSTOPKEY" link "recstop" 0} 
      or open the MUI_ASCSEND-window 

@endnode

@node "recstop" "recstop"
  
      RECSTOPKEY=taste       (MUI_ASCSEND and IREC only)

      stops the recording of keystrokes.
      The keystrokes are then converted into a textfile and written with
      @{"RECFILE" link "recfile" 0} filename

@endnode

@node "recfile" "recfile"
  
      RECFILE=dateiname       (MUI_ASCSEND and IREC only)
      
      The textfile into which the recorded keystrokes are written

@endnode

@node "min_delay" "min_delay"

       MIN_DELAY=50           (MUI_ASCSEND and IREC only)
        
       delay in 1/50 secs. If two recorded InputEvents have more
       delay, a delay-InputEvent (\dxxxx) is written to the file
       
       defaults to  25 (1/4 sec)

@endnode

@node "h_priority" "h_priority"

      HANDER_PRIORITY=100     (MUI_ASCSEND and IREC only)

      Priority of the inputhandler used by the InputEvent-Recorder.
      should be greater than 50.
      defaults to  60


@endnode

@node "include_mb" "include_mb"

      INCLUDE_MB=YES/NO       (MUI_ASCSEND and IREC only)

      
      if YES, Mousebuttons are recorded.

@endnode

@node "include_delay" "(MUI_ASCSEND"


      INCLUDE_DELAY=YES/NO

      if YES , delays between keystrokes are written to the 
      output file

@endnode

@node "rec_maxchar" "(MUI_ASCSEND"

      REC_MAXCHAR=x

      The InputEvent-Recorder will only recognize x characters.
      When these characters are read, it stops recording and
      writes a file. You have to turn tis option on using the
      @{"REC_MAX_ON" link "rec_max_on" 0} tooltype (or MUI_ASCSEND
      function)

@endnode

@node "rec_max_on" "(MUI_ASCSEND"


      REC_MAX_ON=YES/NO
     
      if YES, only the in @{"REC_MAXCHAR" link "rec_maxchar" 0}
      given numbers of InputEvents will be  read.

@endnode

@node "irec_wait" "(IREC"

      WAIT=[ticks]

      can be used on the commandline of IREC (as all other IREC-tooltypes)
      
      If you have set @{"REC_MAX_ON" link "rec_max_on" 0}=YES and @{"REC_MAXCHAR" link "rec_maxchar" 0} > 0 und WAIT > 0,
      then IREC waits x 1/50sec, starts recording and quits after
REC_MAXCHAR characters are
      read. Then it writes the RECFILE and quits.

@endnode

@node "InputEvents" "InputEvents"

      ASCII_SEND recognizes a number of special InputEvents.

   1. key descriptions in angle brackets

      Example
      
      pressing Control-f1: <control-f1>
      
   2. other events   
      
      @{b}\n@{ub}    =  ENTER
      @{b}\r@{ub}    =  RETURN
      @{b}\t@{ub}    =  TAB
      @{b}\d[x]@{ub} Delay in  1/50 Sec
      
            Example: And now for  2 seconds delay : \d100 and on we go...
            
      @{b}\l[x]@{ub} Delay in 1/50 Sec between lines
      
      @{b}\c[x]@{ub} Delay in 1/50 Sekunden between single characters
      
             Example: \c20writing slowly...\c0 and quickly...
            
             HINWEIS: The@{b}\c@{ub} und @{b}\l@{ub} events are only valid
             during the current file

             The delays \d, \c und \l can have up to 4 digits
             use trailing zeroes (as the InputEvent-Recorder) in doubt

      @{b}\(lmd:x,y)@{ub} "Left Mouse Button down" at the Position x,y
                          of the frontmost screen

      @{b}\(lmu:x,y)@{ub} "Left Mouse Button up" at the Position x,y
             
      @{b}\(rmd:x,y)@{ub} "Right Mouse Button down" at the Position x,y
             
      @{b}\(rmu:x,y)@{ub} "Right Mouse Button up" at the Position x,y
             
      @{b}\(mmd:x,y)@{ub} "Middle Mouse Button down" at the Position x,y
             
      @{b}\(mmu:x,y)@{ub} "Middle Mouse Button up" at the Position x,y
             

@endnode

@node "mui-ASCII_SEND" "mui-ASCII_SEND"

      1. When the control window is open, all hotkeys are 
         inactive            
 
      2. when opening the window, transferring files is
         suspended

      3. you can save the settings into the program icon.
         these icon-files can be used with IREC, ASCII_SEND
         and CLI_ASCSEND, too.

         
      4. MUI_ASCSEND has an @{"Arexx" link "arexx" 0}-Port   

@endnode

@node "cli_ascsend" "cli_ascsend"

      CLI_ASCSEND can only be used from a shell.
      
      
      USAGE:
      
      ascsend FILE/A,WINDOW/K/M,SCREEN/K,WAIT/K/N,DELAY/K/N,DELAYCHAR/K/N
      
      FILE/A         textfile to send
     
      WINDOW/K/M     the window to sent the file to. If it doesn't exist,
                     ascsend quits without sending a file

      SCREEN/K       Name of a screen. The file ist sent to the first
                     window of this screen.

      WAIT/K/N       number of ticks (1/50 s) to wait before sending 
                     the file.
     
      @{"DELAY" link "delay" 0} can @{"DELAYCHAR" link "delaychar" 0}
      be used also.

      Example:

       ascsend test.file WINDOW SAS/C Editor WAIT 100

       waits 2 seconds, activates a window called "SAS/C Editor", sends the
       test.file and quits

@endnode

@node "arexx" "arexx"

      These are the arexx-commands of MUI_ASCSEND

command              Parameterr
------------------------------------------------------------------- quit
---------         quits MUI_ASCSEND.
  hide                 ---------         iconify and make MUI_ASCSEND
                                       inactive

show                 ---------         activate the hidden MUI_ASCSEND

openwindow           ---------         open the control window

closewindow          ---------         close the control window

stopkey              ---------         stop sending a file     

infokey              ---------         show the info-requestert

requestkey           ---------         show the filerequester
                                       NOTE: this call is ignored, when the
                                       control window is currently open

send                  FILE/A           send a file
                                       NOTE: If MUI_ASCSEND is currently
                                       sending a file, this call is
                                       ignored

string                STRING/A/M       send the string instead of a file
                                                                            
            activate_window       WINDOW/A         activate the window with
the given
                                       title. if the window is not found
                                       RC_ERROR is returned.
                                        activate_screen SCREEN/A
activate the first window of the
                                       given sreen.
  setkey       FILE/A,KEY/M/A            make a hotkey together with a
                                       file
                                        start_rec    -------
start recording.
                                       NOTE: this call is ignored, when the
                                       control window is currently open

stop_rec     -------                   stop recording.

recfile      FILE/A                    the filename for the InputEvent-
                                       recorder.

rec_options  MIN_DELAY/N,PRI/N,MOUSEBUTTONS/S,DELAYS/S,MAXCHAR/N,ON/S
       
                                       Options of the  InputEvent-Recorders
                                       Example:
                                       rec_options 'MIN_DELAY=30 PRI=90
DELAYS MOUSEBUTTONS'
                                 remove       KEY/M/A
remove a hotkey-file-pair from the
                                       list.
                                       Example:
                                           
                                       remove 'control alt x' removes the
corresponding
                                       key.
                                              remove_all  -
--------        clear the entire hotkey-file-list

set
POPKEY/S,REQUESTKEY/S,INFOKEY/S,STOPKEY/S,RECSTARTKEY/S,RECSTOPKEY/S,KEY/M/A

 
                                       set the keys 
                                       Example:
                                       
                                       set POPKEY 'alt f10' sets
                                       CX_POPKEY to  "alt f10"
                                        delay                   TICKS/N/A
delay between lines

delaychar               TICKS/N/A      delay between characters
                                           reset                   ---------
clear all settings and load them
                                       new from the icon.

saveicon                ----------     write an icon with the current
settings

@endnode

